Sounds like a CTRE drive

First time kraken motor use and swerve drive use Java
You have a whole lot of options to choose from: CTRE Swerve This is the official swerve API from CTRE. It’s designed for ease and consistency, running closed loops directly on hardware and using CTRE features. As @KfirNeuman mentioned, this is a great place to start. YAGSL A community-developed swerve drive library that offers many helpful features like auto-alignment and aim-at-target functionality. It’s an excellent choice if your team has some programming experience and wants high-level fea…
